comments: Hardaway Jr. (DAL) reaches in and makes marginal contact with Randle's (NOP) arm that does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Randle (NOP) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Miller (NOP) reaches in and makes hand-on-ball contact with Hardaway Jr. (DAL) during the drive and the contact is deemed incidental.
Jackson (NOP) and Hardaway Jr. (DAL) engage and disengage off ball in the post.
Jackson (NOP) initiates some contact with Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) body but the contact is marginal and does not affect his driving shot attempt.
Brunson (DAL) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Powell (DAL) moves laterally into the path of Randle (NOP) during his drive and the contact affects his SQBR.
Randle (NOP) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Finney-Smith (DAL) and he is firming up over his right leg when the contact occurs during the screen.
Payton (NOP) cleanly dislodges the ball from Hardaway Jr. (DAL) in the post.
Randle (NOP) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
LLS shows Hardaway Jr. (DAL) applies a forearm to the side of Payton (NOP) and delivers contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Williams (NOP) absorbs the body contact with Brunson (DAL) after he receives the pass.
Randle (NOP) commits a take foul on Doncic (DAL).
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) initiates marginal contact with Williams (NOP) and does not affect his ability to retrieve the loose ball.
Jackson (NOP) and Brunson (DAL) engage in marginal contact during the inbound.
[Observable in enhanced video] Doncic (DAL) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
At the start of the drive, Williams (NOP) loses his balance and places a hand/forearm to Doncic's (DAL) front as he falls to the floor.  The resulting body contact trips Doncic and affects his SQBR.
Powell (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Williams (NOP) and he does not deliver contact during the pick.

At the end of the drive, Payton (NOP) slightly extends his forearm into Doncic's (DAL) body as he is retreating towards the basket. The contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to defend the shot attempt.
Diallo (NOP) and Powell (DAL) both briefly grasp each other's arms during the rebound. The contact is marginal.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) absorbs the body contact and makes incidental contact to Jackson's (NOP) arm after the release that does not affect his driving shot attempt.

Powell (DAL) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Williams (NOP) but he slightly leans forward and delivers some contact. The contact is marginal and does not affect his ability to defend the jump shot attempt.
Miller (NOP) briefly clasps Finney-Smith's (DAL) arm but does not affect his ability to retrieve the rebound.
Diallo (NOP) maintains verticality and absorbs the oncoming body contact with Doncic (DAL) during his driving shot attempt.

Diallo (NOP) never makes contact with the ball when Doncic (DAL) goes up for the shot attempt and the ball never hits the rim or backboard.  Doncic lands and regathers possession of the ball and this is a traveling violation.
Doncic (DAL) commits a take foul on Jackson (NOP).
Jackson (NOP) makes contact to Hardaway Jr.'s (DAL) body during his driving shot attempt.

Payton's (NOP) arm swings back as he dribbles away and he makes inadvertent contact to Doncic's (DAL) head/face. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Doncic (DAL) commits a take foul on Payton (NOP).
As Williams (NOP) absorbs contact from the pick, he brings one hand to the opposite side of Powell's (DAL) body but he immediately removes it.
Harris (DAL) commits a take foul on Miller (NOP).
MOB shows Harris (DAL) makes contact to Miller's (NOP) wrist, affecting his ability to maintain control of the ball and causing him to lose it out of bounds.
